ting their historical contexts, allegorical tropes, and social critiques. Combining eye-opening archival research with fresh interpretations of over fifteen of Brocka's major and minor works, Martial Law Melodrama does more than reveal the breadth of his political vision. It also offers a timely lesson about popular cinema's vital role in the struggle for democracy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aMotion picturesxPolitical aspectszPhilippinesy20th century. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Individual Director (see also BIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Entertainment & Performing Arts).2bisacsh  aallegorical tropes.  aauteur of social films.  abankable director of genre movies.  acinemas role in struggle for democracy.  acritic of ferdinand marcos autocratic regime.  afifteen major and minor works.  afilmmaker.  ahistorical contexts.  alino brocka.  apioneer of queer cinema.  apolitical examination of brockas films.  areveal breadth of political vision.  asocial critiques.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertArt and Architecture eBook-Package 2020z978311073823008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2020z9783110704655oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishz978311070478508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520974012zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520974012423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520974012.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-